Package com.rb.biz.types.asset

Class CashId

java.lang.Object
com.rb.biz.types.asset.AssetId
com.rb.biz.types.asset.CashId
All Implemented Interfaces:
Investable, PrintsInstruments, HasLongRepresentation, java.lang.Comparable<HasLongRepresentation>
public class CashId
extends AssetId
The special AssetId for CASH.

This class allows us to avoid special-casing cash in the code. Sometimes we want to treat cash and securities the same, in which case we use AssetId, which covers more. In other cases, we only want to store information about non-cash / securities, in which case we use InstrumentId.

Unlike InstrumentId, one cannot construct a CashId. The only available instance is CASH, which is given the special numeric ID of 0L. Although the cleaner way to determine whether an AssetId is a CashId or an InstrumentId is via an AssetId.AssetIdVisitor, this special numeric code ( CASH_ID ) makes it easier to make that determination in a faster way.

See Also:
AssetId, InstrumentId
